Facebook GIT Challenge
Mark went
Git is widely adopted in the e-org and there have been many success stories of increased productivity (e.g. multitasking with local branches/checkpoints, debugging with git-bisect, etc.) from everyone who's tried it. The Facebook GIT challenge is as follows: 1) Install Git, and for a FULL 2 1/2 WEEKS, use it for the MAJORITY of your checkins into the PHP codebase. 2) After your 2 1/2 weeks are up, write on the wall of this event with your testimonial on whether (or not) your productivity has significantly increased because of GIT. At the end of February, all participants who manage to go a FULL 2 1/2 weeks on GIT will be taken out to a free lunch by the Git mailing list community. GET STARTED HERE: http://www.dev.facebook.com/intern/wiki/index.php/Gitfaq http://www.dev.facebook.com/intern/wiki/images//b/b4/Gitfaq--git.pdf FOR EXISTING GIT USERS - The "PLUS" Challenge For users who already enjoy the benefits of GIT, there's some "plus" challenges that you can attempt: e.g. - use git bisect during a push for debugging, etc. - pipe git diff to diffcamp, or use diffcamp -gs - merge an svn branch using git (please feel free to add your "plus" challenge to the wall)
Friday, January 30, 2009 at 4:00pm - Saturday, February 28, 2009 at 7:00pm in PST

Impromptu 31st Birthday Bowling Extravaganza
Mark went
Tomorrow I turn 31 and have decided to celebrate like i'm 11! Come bowl, drink beer, and enjoy some general debauchery like we used to back in 5th grade! I've reserved 4 lanes but will expand if needed. Please feel free to bring whoever as long as they bring a night of mayhem like attitude. This also means you should feel free to dress up in some ridiculous fashion. Finally, this was a last minute decision which is why you're getting this invite today but I can't imagine you have better Monday night plans. OK, onto the rules. 1. There are three prizes for the 3 top scores - A coozy made of beads you can hang around your neck, a shark water gun, and a squeezable alien thing. Top score gets first choice, second best score gets second choice, and so on. 2. Highest score will have to wear a Sweet 16 Sash so everyone knows how sweet they are. When someone gets a higher score they will relinquish that sash and finish their drink. 3. Lowest score will wear the Yellow Boa of Swallowing Sadness. If someone then gets a lower score they will have to don the Boa and finish their drink. 4. If you get 2 gutter balls in a row you have to perform some ridiculous old school dance - kid n’ play, running man, etc. 5. For every strike you get you can make someone take a drink. 6. If you get a turkey you have to bowl the next frame with your non-dominant hand. 7. If you get two spares in two consecutive frames you get to choose someone to have to bowl their next shot with their non-dominant hand. 8. If you bowl two prime numbers in a row you have to bowl backwards on your next shot. Please leave additional rules in the comments and we'll add them to the official rule set. See y'all tomorrow!
Monday, March 22, 2010, 8:00 PM - 10:30 PM in PDT
AMF Bowling Center in Redwood City,2580 El Camino Real,Redwood City,California,United States
